Date:  0/0/1988
Source:  Through the Looking Glass
Author:
Vol / Page:  125
Edition:
Quote:  My brothers' slang and `funny' sayings delighted me. ... i remember [126] such words as `batty', `hoot' and `spondulicks' and many that ... were corruptions of Maori words. i spell them here as they sounded to  me then: ehoa, harka, kupai, kure, munga munga  typo, markuta, pooku, tangy.
Notes:  (Meikle)
